  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.78 sitting just below the massive +6732.8M gamma wall at 6600, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The 12.3B total GEX in PIN regime creates a strong gravitational pull around current levels, with dealers acting as stabilizers by fading momentum in both directions. Key inflection point is the 6648 flip strike - any sustained break above shifts dealers from stabilizing to amplifying mode, while a drop toward 6500 (-4480.6M) triggers dealer buying support.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned near 6600 with dealers capping upside rallies.",
